  "handoff_packets": [
    {
      "content": "{\n  \"cwd\": \"/Users/sam.zhang/Documents/codex-supervisor\",\n  \"execution_layer_policy\": {\n    \"agentic_lead_policy\": {\n      \"min_subagents\": 0,\n      \"policy\": \"off\",\n      \"required_evidence_grade\": \"self_reported\",\n      \"required_roles\": [],\n      \"solo_exception_for_artifact_only_gates\": false\n    },\n    \"allowed_dynamic_workflow_task_classes\": [],\n    \"codex_supervises_final_artifact\": true,\n    \"dynamic_workflow_task_class\": null,\n    \"lead_execution_layer\": \"single_lead_worker\",\n    \"mode\": \"lead_direct\",\n    \"preview_required_gates\": [],\n    \"supervision_layer\": \"codex_plus_lead\"\n  },\n  \"expected_decisions\": [],\n  \"expected_objections\": [],\n  \"expected_specialists\": [],\n  \"gate\": \"tdd_review\",\n  \"instruction\": \"Supervisor-owned workflow gate: tdd_review.\\n\\nIntent:\\nMake the Cursor independent reviewer path either return a valid typed outcome or fail with a deterministic, recoverable, typed artifact, so a reviewer that ran but produced no parseable verdict is classified as an infrastructure failure with a documented recovery path instead of hard-blocking the gate in limbo indistinguishable from a quality rejection. EXACT PROBLEM: invoke_cursor_agent in supervisor/cursor_agent.py calls evaluate_outcome_fidelity. When Cursor output lacks a parseable <dual_agent_outcome> block, fidelity fails with missing dual_agent_outcome, then is recorded as cursor_review_failed and the gate blocks. The gate cannot distinguish Cursor returned REVISE or DENY from Cursor never returned a valid verdict. Scope: add bounded corrective retries in cursor_agent.py; terminal failure becomes typed reviewer_infrastructure_unavailable or reviewer_contract_unmet without fabricating an outcome; classify and recover at the gate/policy layer in mcp_tools/codex_supervisor_stdio.py without counting missing verdict as accept and without bypassing gates; persist reviewer verdict/classification to ledger so Transport closed during read_gate_transcript cannot lose it. Non-goals: do not change AND semantics for real verdicts, do not auto-accept missing verdicts, do not weaken P1/P2/P3/P13/P14 or independent review, do not build lower-level MCP reconnect. Acceptance: valid Cursor typed outcome behaves normally; malformed/no outcome retries then records deterministic infrastructure artifact and classification; genuine Cursor revise/deny still blocks; simulated Transport closed during transcript read does not lose persisted reviewer verdict; no missing verdict counted as accept; suite stays green; typed outcome plus reviewer pass on this run.\\n\\nReview this gate against the current source artifacts and return a typed dual_agent_outcome.\\nUse decisions/objections to say whether the gate should accept, revise, or deny.\\n\\nCorrective context from the previous round:\\ncursor_review_failed: missing dual_agent_outcome block\",\n  \"lead_skill\": null,\n  \"outcome_validation_policy\": {\n    \"fidelity_failure\": \"abort_to_operator\",\n    \"malformed_outcome\": \"retry_once_with_corrective_packet\",\n    \"subprocess_failure\": \"abort_to_operator\",\n    \"timeout\": \"abort_to_operator\"\n  },\n  \"packet_schema_version\": \"dual-agent-handoff/v1\",\n  \"planning_artifacts\": [\n    {\n      \"kind\": \"prd\",\n      \"mutable_by_worker\": false,\n      \"path\": \"docs/dual-agent/cursor-review-reliability-20260531/source/prd.md\",\n      \"sha256\": \"6fdddc0e2f6ef058aabc4bac7a38af763e1890950e483c16d129e4a0e1e05a67\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"kind\": \"grill_findings\",\n      \"mutable_by_worker\": false,\n      \"path\": \"docs/dual-agent/cursor-review-reliability-20260531/source/grill-findings.md\",\n      \"sha256\": \"555b43e61b03773c3437a6f3524493d0e2f012dac00987002c489f8094d5c895\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"kind\": \"issues\",\n      \"mutable_by_worker\": false,\n      \"path\": \"docs/dual-agent/cursor-review-reliability-20260531/source/issues.md\",\n     